WEBVTT

00:09.240 --> 00:10.340
- Are you ready, kids?

00:10.342 --> 00:12.309
<i>all:</i>
<i>Aye, aye, Captain!</i>

00:12.311 --> 00:13.610
- I can't hear you.

00:13.612 --> 00:16.113
<i>all:</i>
<i>Aye, aye, Captain!</i>

00:16.114 --> 00:18.215
- ♪ Ohh... ♪

00:18.217 --> 00:20.717
<i>♪ Who lives in a pineapple</i>
<i>under the sea? ♪</i>

00:20.719 --> 00:22.319
<i>all:</i>
<i>SpongeBob SquarePants!</i>

00:22.321 --> 00:24.621
<i>- ♪ Absorbent and yellow</i>
<i>and porous is he ♪</i>

00:24.623 --> 00:25.856
<i>all:</i>
<i>SpongeBob SquarePants!</i>

00:25.858 --> 00:28.759
<i>- ♪ If nautical nonsense</i>
<i>be something you wish ♪</i>

00:28.761 --> 00:30.193
<i>all:</i>
<i>SpongeBob SquarePants!</i>

00:30.195 --> 00:32.462
<i>- ♪ Then drop on the deck</i>
<i>and flop like a fish ♪</i>

00:32.464 --> 00:34.731
<i>all: SpongeBob SquarePants!</i>
<i>- Ready?</i>

00:34.733 --> 00:36.833
<i>all:</i>
<i>SpongeBob SquarePants!</i>

00:36.835 --> 00:39.169
<i>SpongeBob SquarePants!</i>

00:39.171 --> 00:41.204
<i>SpongeBob SquarePants!</i>

00:41.206 --> 00:42.539
<i>- SpongeBob</i>

00:42.541 --> 00:44.441
<i>SquarePants!</i>

00:44.443 --> 00:47.244
<i>[laughing]</i>

00:47.246 --> 00:49.112
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:49.114 --> 00:50.814
<i>[waves crashing]</i>

00:52.000 --> 00:58.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:04.861 --> 01:06.596
- Ooh!

01:06.598 --> 01:09.666
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

01:09.668 --> 01:14.304
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:14.306 --> 01:15.305
[line trilling]

01:15.307 --> 01:17.441
[car lock beeps]

01:17.443 --> 01:19.743
[indistinct conversations]

01:19.745 --> 01:21.611
- Hi, Pearl.
- Hey, girl!

01:21.613 --> 01:23.914
Let's hang out!
- Ugh, I can't.

01:23.916 --> 01:26.316
I have to work
at Hot Dog on a String today.

01:26.318 --> 01:30.887
Brad called in sick, so I'm
in charge of stringing the dogs.

01:30.889 --> 01:32.255
Totally lame.

01:32.257 --> 01:35.659
- I guess
I'll see you later then.

01:35.661 --> 01:36.526
- Uh...

01:36.528 --> 01:40.297
Can I get one with,
uh, extra string?

01:40.299 --> 01:42.466
- Ugh.

01:42.468 --> 01:43.700
<i>[heavy metal guitar tones]</i>

01:43.702 --> 01:44.734
[phone screaming]

01:44.736 --> 01:46.336
- What?
- Hey, girl!

01:46.338 --> 01:49.506
Want to come over and make fun
of boys or something?

01:49.508 --> 01:52.008
- Uh, sorry, girl,
I can't.

01:52.010 --> 01:54.678
I'm working at Scorched Coral
all day.

01:54.680 --> 01:56.413
It's heinous.

01:56.415 --> 01:57.414
- Oh!
[laughs]

01:57.416 --> 02:00.550
So heinous.
See ya later.

02:00.552 --> 02:02.385
- See ya later, Pearl.

02:02.387 --> 02:04.488
- How much is this choker?

02:04.490 --> 02:06.723
- Um, it's a wrist band.

02:06.725 --> 02:09.025
- [gasping and choking]

02:09.026 --> 02:10.660
- Awesome.

02:10.662 --> 02:12.629
<i>[light instrumental music]</i>

02:12.631 --> 02:14.030
[phone rings]
- Nixie speaking.

02:14.032 --> 02:19.336
- Nixie! My bestest friend
in the whole wide world.

02:19.338 --> 02:20.370
You should come over.

02:20.372 --> 02:23.640
We can watch TV
<i>and</i> eat cheese!

02:23.642 --> 02:24.508
- I wish I could, Pearl,

02:24.510 --> 02:26.343
but I have to work
at Dangles and Bangles.

02:26.345 --> 02:29.346
All dangles are half off with
the purchase of any bangle.

02:29.348 --> 02:31.948
Dangle must be of equal
or lesser value than bangle.

02:31.950 --> 02:34.684
Some restrictions may apply.

02:35.586 --> 02:40.457
- Oh, you don't work
at the mall, do you, Derek?

02:40.459 --> 02:43.760
- No, but all my girlfriends do.

02:43.762 --> 02:45.862
[ding]

02:45.864 --> 02:48.999
- Daddy!
Guess what?

02:49.001 --> 02:50.033
- [gasps]

02:50.035 --> 02:52.302
[muttering frantically]

02:52.304 --> 02:55.005
[chuckles]
I have no idea, Pearly.

02:55.007 --> 02:58.408
- Dad, I'm getting a job today.

02:58.410 --> 02:59.709
- [shouts]

02:59.711 --> 03:00.911
Yahoo!

03:00.913 --> 03:04.514
Oh, this is great news,
Pearl, me dear!

03:04.516 --> 03:06.516
Now instead of wasting
my precious money

03:06.518 --> 03:09.853
on your "clothes"
and your "school supplies"...

03:09.855 --> 03:12.422
[chuckles]
You can waste your own.

03:12.424 --> 03:14.391
- I'll be a independent
working woman,

03:14.393 --> 03:18.562
blazing my own trail and
standing on my own two fins.

03:18.564 --> 03:20.063
- That's the spirit.

03:20.065 --> 03:21.765
- Oh, can I borrow $10?

03:21.767 --> 03:23.433
[cash register chimes]

03:23.435 --> 03:25.068
- I'll miss you
around the house.

03:25.070 --> 03:27.771
- Oh, Daddy, you'll see me
after work.

03:27.773 --> 03:30.740
- I was talkin' to the money.

03:31.642 --> 03:32.642
- Hey, Marina!

03:32.644 --> 03:34.511
I'm here to apply for a job.

03:34.513 --> 03:37.814
- You should meet the manager,
I guess?

03:37.816 --> 03:38.715
He's in his office.

03:38.717 --> 03:44.688
Mr. Pepalino, there's someone
here for a job.

03:44.690 --> 03:45.922
- Ah!

03:45.924 --> 03:47.490
- [straining]

03:47.492 --> 03:50.927
- [grunting and groaning]

03:50.929 --> 03:53.029
I-I don't think he's in there.

03:53.031 --> 03:55.565
- [muffled moaning]

03:55.567 --> 03:59.002
[mumbling]

03:59.004 --> 04:02.906
[groaning]

04:02.908 --> 04:06.509
[gargling]

04:06.511 --> 04:08.912
[steam hissing]

04:09.847 --> 04:12.582
We're not hiring.

04:12.850 --> 04:14.084
<i>[heavy metal guitar tones]</i>

04:14.086 --> 04:17.053
- Welcome to Scorched Coral.
Please go away.

04:17.055 --> 04:19.689
Oh, hey, Pearl.
What are you doing here?

04:19.690 --> 04:22.592
- I would like to apply
for a job, please.

04:22.594 --> 04:24.594
- Yeah, sorry.
You're a little late.

04:24.596 --> 04:29.099
We <i> were</i> hiring, but we actually
just hired someone today.

04:29.101 --> 04:31.167
- [hissing and growling]

04:31.169 --> 04:32.902
- Ah!

04:33.104 --> 04:36.539
Oh, Nixie, I need to work
at Dangles and Bangles.

04:36.541 --> 04:39.409
This is my last chance.
You gotta help me out here.

04:39.411 --> 04:41.411
Oh, please, please, please,
please, please!

04:41.413 --> 04:44.948
- Come on, let me introduce you
to the manager.

04:45.516 --> 04:47.183
- This is--
- Nope, not hiring.

04:47.185 --> 04:49.786
- You don't understand.
I have to work here!

04:49.788 --> 04:53.990
- Sorry, missy, the only thing
we don't dangle here

04:53.992 --> 04:55.625
is hope.

04:55.627 --> 04:57.527
- Oh, bangles.

04:58.029 --> 05:01.431
<i>[tropical music]</i>

05:01.433 --> 05:03.733
Ah...

05:05.870 --> 05:07.971
[belches]

05:08.539 --> 05:10.507
Oh, this is the worst.

05:10.509 --> 05:12.175
If I don't get a job
at the mall,

05:12.177 --> 05:16.179
I'm gonna have to hang out
with my dad.

05:16.181 --> 05:17.080
[sighs]

05:17.082 --> 05:18.915
- You looking for a job,
deary?

05:18.917 --> 05:21.518
- Yeah!
I need one as soon as possible.

05:21.520 --> 05:24.521
It's a life or death situation,
actually.

05:24.523 --> 05:26.089
- Oh, my goodness.

05:26.091 --> 05:26.956
Are you in danger?

05:26.958 --> 05:28.758
- In danger
of never seeing my friends

05:28.760 --> 05:30.960
'cause I don't have a job.

05:30.962 --> 05:33.530
- Come with me.

05:37.134 --> 05:38.234
[glass shattering]

05:38.236 --> 05:39.602
- [gasps]
Weird.

05:39.604 --> 05:42.639
[alarm blaring]
[whistle blowing]

05:42.641 --> 05:47.911
I've never been in this part
of the mall before.

05:48.546 --> 05:50.013
[gasps]
Ugh!

05:50.015 --> 05:50.914
What's that smell?

05:50.916 --> 05:54.984
- Oh, probably one of the many
perfumes that we sell

05:54.986 --> 05:58.788
here at Grandma's Apron!

05:59.590 --> 06:02.692
Congratulations!
You're hired.

06:02.694 --> 06:03.326
- [gasps]

06:03.328 --> 06:07.831
Oh, this is the best day
of my life!

06:07.833 --> 06:09.099
- [groaning]

06:09.101 --> 06:10.033
Ah!
[back pops]

06:10.035 --> 06:13.536
Well, I can't quite afford
to be picky these days.

06:13.538 --> 06:17.273
The only other employee
besides me was Myrtle,

06:17.275 --> 06:21.711
and she's...no longer with us.

06:21.713 --> 06:25.782
- [shrieks]
Almost forgot my shades!

06:26.217 --> 06:28.551
See ya later, suckers!

06:28.553 --> 06:30.653
[laughing]

06:32.223 --> 06:34.758
- Hey, Pearl.
Over here.

06:34.760 --> 06:35.658
- Did you find a job?

06:35.660 --> 06:40.063
- Yeah, I got a job
at Grandma's Apron.

06:40.065 --> 06:44.801
- [laughing]
Pearl, you can not be serious.

06:44.803 --> 06:47.036
- Ew, that store is
for old people.

06:47.038 --> 06:51.107
- [laughing]
Old people are so...old.

06:51.109 --> 06:53.843
- Old people aren't that bad.

06:53.845 --> 06:55.945
Are they?

06:57.314 --> 06:59.282
- [mumbling]

06:59.284 --> 07:00.583
- [slurping]

07:00.585 --> 07:03.086
[laughter]

07:05.990 --> 07:09.092
<i>[ragtime music]</i>

07:09.094 --> 07:10.727
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:10.729 --> 07:13.863
- Hey, girls,
I smell moth balls.

07:13.865 --> 07:15.965
- Well, we are having a sale
on them.

07:15.967 --> 07:17.200
They're 25% off today.

07:17.202 --> 07:19.936
- Um, isn't it
your nap time, Pearl?

07:19.938 --> 07:23.006
- Where's your muumuu, granny?

07:23.008 --> 07:24.974
[laughter]

07:24.976 --> 07:28.778
- Oh, don't let those
bubble-headed nincompoops

07:28.780 --> 07:30.013
get to you, Pearly.

07:30.015 --> 07:31.948
- But it's not fair.

07:31.950 --> 07:33.983
- Life's not fair, my dear.

07:33.985 --> 07:37.120
We all go through hard times
at some point.

07:37.122 --> 07:38.721
Here, look.
See?

07:38.723 --> 07:41.090
I was different
from the other girls,

07:41.092 --> 07:42.692
and they teased me for it.

07:42.694 --> 07:45.128
They called me
"Boring Beatrice."

07:45.130 --> 07:48.031
Not very creative, those girls.
[chuckles]

07:48.033 --> 07:49.699
- Who would even
take a picture of that?

07:49.701 --> 07:54.170
- Oh, good ol' Jonesy
from the AV Club took that one!

07:54.172 --> 07:55.839
- Wait, but who took
<i>that</i> picture--

07:55.841 --> 07:58.141
- All that matters,
Pearly, my dear,

07:58.143 --> 08:00.910
is that things will soon change.

08:00.912 --> 08:01.711
But in the meantime,

08:01.713 --> 08:03.980
you should be having
as much fun as possible.

08:03.982 --> 08:07.951
Let me show you
how grandmas do it.

08:08.686 --> 08:11.788
<i>[jazz music]</i>

08:11.790 --> 08:20.129
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:29.006 --> 08:31.241
[explosion]

08:31.243 --> 08:33.977
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:33.979 --> 08:36.011
[laughter]

08:36.014 --> 08:39.282
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:39.284 --> 08:42.952
- Whoa, come back here, yarn!

08:42.953 --> 08:44.087
[panting]

08:44.089 --> 08:44.954
[all gasp]

08:44.956 --> 08:46.256
<i>[dramatic tones]</i>

08:46.258 --> 08:49.359
- [laughing]
Love the shoes, Pearl.

08:49.361 --> 08:51.394
- You guys just don't get it.

08:51.396 --> 08:53.162
Being a grandma is fun.

08:53.164 --> 08:56.065
<i>I get to sit</i>
<i>in a rocking chair,</i>

08:56.067 --> 08:57.767
<i>dust tchotchkes,</i>

08:57.769 --> 08:58.501
<i>bake cookies,</i>

08:58.503 --> 09:01.738
<i>knit mittens,</i>
<i>hats, and scarves.</i>

09:01.740 --> 09:04.007
[laughter]

09:04.009 --> 09:04.707
- Scarves.

09:04.709 --> 09:08.311
- It's actually, like, the most
coral store in the whole mall,

09:08.313 --> 09:14.751
so you can all just...just...
eat barnacles!

09:14.753 --> 09:16.119
[laughter]

09:16.121 --> 09:19.422
- Now, now, girls.
Let's be polite.

09:19.424 --> 09:23.793
- What are you gonna do
about it, granny?

09:23.795 --> 09:26.963
[grunting menacingly]

09:26.965 --> 09:28.831
- Granny power!

09:28.833 --> 09:31.234
[echoing]
Power! Power!

09:31.236 --> 09:32.168
- Aah!

09:32.170 --> 09:33.169
- [growls]

09:33.171 --> 09:36.973
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

09:36.975 --> 09:38.141
- Aah!

09:38.143 --> 09:40.476
[all screaming]

09:40.478 --> 09:44.847
- Pearl, toss me
the Autumn Years perfume.

09:44.849 --> 09:46.115
- Hi-ya!

09:46.117 --> 09:50.987
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:50.989 --> 09:52.322
[all screaming]

09:52.324 --> 09:55.825
- It smells like pills
and bed pans.

09:55.827 --> 09:56.993
Whoa!

09:56.995 --> 10:02.265
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:02.267 --> 10:05.134
- [laughing]

10:05.136 --> 10:08.004
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:08.006 --> 10:10.206
[all whimpering]

10:10.774 --> 10:13.209
- Well, now that
you're all sitting down,

10:13.211 --> 10:14.978
let me tell you
about the first time

10:14.980 --> 10:17.213
I ever saw a talking
picture show.

10:17.215 --> 10:19.949
Oh, boy, did they know
how to talk.

10:19.951 --> 10:23.319
- No, please!
I can't take any more!

10:23.321 --> 10:26.389
- It's... so...boring.

10:26.391 --> 10:29.092
- No, I hate the past.

10:29.927 --> 10:34.497
- And that's why today,
we all wear shoes.

10:34.499 --> 10:36.866
- Okay, okay,
We get it.

10:36.868 --> 10:39.502
We will stop being mean,
I promise.

10:39.504 --> 10:42.305
Just let us go.

10:43.173 --> 10:45.141
all: Whoa!

10:45.143 --> 10:46.876
[all groaning]

10:46.878 --> 10:47.543
- Listen, Pearl.

10:47.545 --> 10:49.345
We didn't mean to hurt
your feeling or anything.

10:49.347 --> 10:52.248
We just, like, think it's weird
that you're, like,

10:52.250 --> 10:55.118
a grandma now or whatever.

10:55.120 --> 10:56.519
We don't really get it.

10:56.521 --> 11:00.156
- Well, I don't care
what you think anymore anyway.

11:00.158 --> 11:01.557
I'm being true to myself,

11:01.559 --> 11:05.928
and--and that's all
that matters!

11:05.930 --> 11:07.397
all: Eh.

11:08.098 --> 11:10.500
- I'm a grandma now.
Right, Beatrice?

11:10.502 --> 11:15.371
- Oh, Pearl, I'm so glad
you enjoy being a grandma,

11:15.373 --> 11:17.974
but your friends
make a good point.

11:17.976 --> 11:20.109
You're only young once, you see.

11:20.111 --> 11:22.478
You don't want
to grow up too fast

11:22.480 --> 11:26.182
or you'll miss out
on all the fun.

11:26.184 --> 11:28.317
- I guess you're right.

11:28.319 --> 11:30.253
Being a grandma is nice and all,

11:30.255 --> 11:33.523
but I do miss
being a super hip young person.

11:33.525 --> 11:37.026
- Go have yourself some fun,
my dear.

11:37.028 --> 11:37.860
Ah, ah, ah, ah.

11:37.862 --> 11:41.264
How 'bout a nice,
gentle handshake instead?

11:41.266 --> 11:43.232
[groans]
- Hey, wait up, guys!

11:43.234 --> 11:46.469
I want to be friends
while I'm still young!

11:46.471 --> 11:49.972
- I'll see you tomorrow.

11:49.974 --> 11:52.041
- You dropped this.

12:04.354 --> 12:06.989
together:
One, two, three, four.

12:06.991 --> 12:08.925
I declare a thumb war!

12:08.927 --> 12:11.561
[both straining]

12:11.563 --> 12:13.563
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

12:13.565 --> 12:14.997
- Huh?
- Yah!

12:14.999 --> 12:17.467
[bell dinging]
[laughter]

12:17.469 --> 12:21.237
- Now that was
a great thumb war, mister.

12:21.239 --> 12:24.974
- It was Patrick, but now
we will let peace prevail.

12:24.976 --> 12:25.775
Let us sign this treaty,

12:25.777 --> 12:29.045
and our thumbs will live
in harmony.

12:29.047 --> 12:30.646
[laughter]

12:30.648 --> 12:31.981
Great job, Patrick.

12:31.983 --> 12:35.952
- Gee, thanks, SpongeBob.
That means a lot.

12:35.954 --> 12:41.224
- Wow, giving someone
a thumbs-up feels great!

12:41.425 --> 12:43.626
- Boy, these Krabby Patties
are delicious.

12:43.628 --> 12:46.596
- I'll say.
They're absolutely stupendous.

12:46.598 --> 12:51.634
- Well, you guys
are stupendous customers.

12:51.636 --> 12:52.335
- [gasps]

12:52.337 --> 12:55.004
That thumbs-up
really touched my heart.

12:55.006 --> 12:55.671
- Yeah, me too.

12:55.673 --> 12:59.642
It's like there's a thumbprint
of happiness on my aorta.

12:59.644 --> 13:01.711
[heart thumps]

13:01.713 --> 13:04.247
- [humming like a train]

13:05.349 --> 13:06.082
Flipping.

13:06.084 --> 13:08.251
- SpongeBob,
you shifty sea-slacker,

13:08.253 --> 13:11.521
have you counted the cups
like I told you to do?

13:11.523 --> 13:13.623
- I sure have, Mr. Krabs.

13:13.625 --> 13:14.257
Five.

13:14.259 --> 13:16.459
But thanks for being
on top of the situation.

13:16.461 --> 13:18.294
You're a fantastic boss.

13:18.296 --> 13:19.395
- Well, thank you.

13:19.397 --> 13:21.364
That's nice of you to say.

13:21.366 --> 13:24.100
Now back to work!

13:24.102 --> 13:26.035
- Yes, sir!

13:28.605 --> 13:29.338
- Oh, SpongeBob,

13:29.340 --> 13:32.775
do you have one of
your precious thumbs-up for me?

13:32.777 --> 13:37.113
I would just love to get one.
[snickers]

13:37.115 --> 13:42.485
- No, Squidward, I do not have
a thumbs-up for you.

13:43.353 --> 13:45.755
I've got two thumbs-up!

13:45.757 --> 13:49.592
- Oh.
That's...thank you.

13:49.594 --> 13:50.626
I think.

13:50.628 --> 13:52.495
- [whistling]

13:52.497 --> 13:54.197
Whoo!

13:55.065 --> 13:59.168
Hey, Sandy, I'm giving
your outfit two thumbs-up.

13:59.170 --> 14:00.770
- [giggles]
This old thing?

14:00.772 --> 14:02.371
It's just something I threw on.

14:02.373 --> 14:06.275
- Well, girl,
you really make it work.

14:06.277 --> 14:08.411
- Okay.

14:08.413 --> 14:11.547
<i>[laid-back music]</i>

14:11.549 --> 14:13.616
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:13.618 --> 14:16.786
- Excuse me, I'm trying
to find the Goo Lagoon

14:16.788 --> 14:17.787
and I'm totally lost.

14:17.789 --> 14:22.658
- Great job on not being afraid
to ask for directions.

14:22.660 --> 14:26.495
Hm...that way?
Okay.

14:27.064 --> 14:30.266
- You got the right stuff,
golden boys.

14:30.268 --> 14:32.535
- SpongeBob, don't you think
that you may be using

14:32.537 --> 14:35.471
the thumbs-up
just a teensy bit too much?

14:35.473 --> 14:36.305
- Are you kidding?

14:36.307 --> 14:39.542
The thumbs-up is an iconic,
internationally-recognized sign

14:39.544 --> 14:41.310
of positivity and affirmation.

14:41.312 --> 14:42.311
Boop!
- Yeah, I know.

14:42.313 --> 14:46.249
But when you do it all the time,
the thumbs-up loses its meaning.

14:46.251 --> 14:48.584
It becomes not special.

14:48.586 --> 14:49.552
- Well, I happen to think

14:49.554 --> 14:53.122
you can never give
too many thumbs-up.

14:53.124 --> 14:54.624
- I don't know, SpongeBob.

14:54.626 --> 14:55.758
I think you should be careful.

14:55.760 --> 14:59.128
- Oh, Sandy, don't be
such a worry whale.

14:59.130 --> 15:01.130
What could go wrong?

15:03.166 --> 15:05.334
[humming]

15:05.336 --> 15:05.868
Ah.

15:05.870 --> 15:10.473
Whoo, I'm giving away
thumbs-up today.

15:10.841 --> 15:14.443
Hey, guy.
Way to wait.

15:14.445 --> 15:15.878
- Who, me?

15:15.880 --> 15:17.847
<i>[playful music]</i>

15:17.849 --> 15:21.651
Yeah...
[whistling]

15:21.653 --> 15:26.689
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:26.691 --> 15:30.293
- Hey, guy.
Way to walk.

15:30.295 --> 15:31.360
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:31.362 --> 15:32.428
- [whimpers]

15:32.430 --> 15:33.329
[tires squealing]

15:33.331 --> 15:36.699
[thud]
- Oh, this feels great.

15:36.701 --> 15:41.671
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:41.673 --> 15:45.808
- Way to flick that eye booger--

15:47.210 --> 15:48.644
[train whistles blowing]

15:48.646 --> 15:51.814
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

15:51.816 --> 15:53.215
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:53.217 --> 15:55.217
[cawing]

15:55.219 --> 15:56.886
[baby crying]

15:56.888 --> 15:58.187
- Thumbhawk one.
Thumbhawk one.

15:58.189 --> 15:59.922
This is Thumbhawk two.
We got two thumbs down.

15:59.924 --> 16:01.390
Repeat.
Two thumbs down!

16:01.392 --> 16:03.192
- Thumbhawk one here, copy that.

16:03.194 --> 16:04.827
Initiate emergency procedures.

16:04.829 --> 16:06.796
- Initiating on my count.

16:06.798 --> 16:08.531
Three, two, one.

16:08.533 --> 16:10.933
[screaming]

16:10.935 --> 16:13.703
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:13.705 --> 16:16.605
- Oh, my thumbs.
My thumbs!

16:16.607 --> 16:21.177
My thumbs!

16:24.648 --> 16:25.815
How's it looking, Dr. Manfish?

16:25.817 --> 16:28.784
- Well, I'm afraid it
doesn't look good, SpongeBob.

16:28.786 --> 16:32.588
It seems you've severely damaged
your ulnar collateral ligament,

16:32.590 --> 16:36.192
possible from
some kind of repeated action.

16:36.194 --> 16:38.394
- An action like a thumbs-up?

16:38.396 --> 16:40.262
- Certainly
that is one possibility.

16:40.264 --> 16:41.297
Hitchhiking could be another.

16:41.299 --> 16:45.234
- But doctor, I will be able
to use my thumbs again, right?

16:45.802 --> 16:48.671
- SpongeBob,
I can't say that for certain.

16:48.673 --> 16:51.540
I'm only a board certified
thumbologist.

16:51.542 --> 16:52.508
I don't know everything.

16:52.510 --> 16:56.212
I can only say that we must
give it time and see.

16:56.214 --> 16:57.380
There are limits to science.

16:57.382 --> 16:59.515
But you should prepare yourself
for the possibility

16:59.517 --> 17:04.753
that you may never regain
the use of your thumbs again.

17:07.257 --> 17:08.991
- [coughing]

17:09.326 --> 17:13.496
- All right, you boneless
invertebrate lazy bones...

17:13.498 --> 17:14.396
[chuckles]
Come on.

17:14.398 --> 17:18.334
Flip them patties, boy-o,
just like the old days.

17:18.336 --> 17:21.369
- Aye aye, Mr. Krabs.

17:23.773 --> 17:25.974
[straining]

17:26.609 --> 17:29.345
- Uh, let me give you a hand.
My thumbs work.

17:29.347 --> 17:31.881
- No!
I can do it.

17:32.783 --> 17:35.918
[groans]

17:38.822 --> 17:41.290
[straining]

17:41.292 --> 17:42.992
[slap]

17:44.494 --> 17:48.497
- I'm sorry, son, but I have
a business to run.

17:48.499 --> 17:49.598
I'm gonna have to let you go.

17:49.600 --> 17:52.802
- That's okay, Mr. Krabs.
I understand.

17:52.804 --> 17:55.905
- Now where's me
new fry cook?

17:55.907 --> 17:58.340
There he is!
Come on in here.

17:58.342 --> 17:59.909
- [straining]

17:59.911 --> 18:02.011
[grill sizzling]

18:02.013 --> 18:05.314
Uh, sorry, SpongeBob.

18:06.883 --> 18:08.584
- Patrick, I'm glad it's you.

18:08.586 --> 18:11.287
Better than some
weird stranger, right?

18:11.289 --> 18:13.422
- Uh, yeah, I guess.

18:13.424 --> 18:18.327
I probably won't even be able
to do good flipping.

18:18.329 --> 18:21.997
- With a little practice,
you could do anything.

18:21.999 --> 18:25.334
[groans]
Oh...

18:25.336 --> 18:26.535
[all gasp]

18:26.537 --> 18:28.904
- Ol' Patty flippin' patties.

18:28.906 --> 18:30.539
Who'd a' thunk it, huh?

18:30.541 --> 18:32.308
[all laugh sadly]

18:32.310 --> 18:33.909
- Poor kid.

18:34.744 --> 18:35.644
<i>[somber music]</i>

18:35.646 --> 18:38.314
<i>- ♪ Thumbs are opposable,</i>
<i>thumbs are great ♪</i>

18:38.316 --> 18:41.383
<i>♪ We share them with</i>
<i>the monkeys and with the apes ♪</i>

18:41.385 --> 18:44.353
<i>♪ You can grab, you can tie,</i>
<i>you can pinch a cheek ♪</i>

18:44.355 --> 18:48.090
<i>all: ♪ But without your thumbs,</i>
<i>you're all thumbs ♪</i>

18:48.092 --> 18:50.025
<i>♪ All thumbs,</i>
<i>no thumbs ♪</i>

18:50.027 --> 18:51.393
<i>♪ Busted up your thumbs ♪</i>

18:51.395 --> 18:53.729
<i>♪ Sucking on your pinkie</i>
<i>would sure look dumb ♪</i>

18:53.731 --> 18:57.099
<i>- ♪ You'll never hitch a ride</i>
<i>or pull out a plum ♪</i>

18:57.101 --> 19:01.003
<i>all: ♪ Without your thumbs,</i>
<i>you're all thumbs ♪</i>

19:01.005 --> 19:02.071
<i>- ♪ Thumbs, thumbs ♪</i>

19:02.073 --> 19:04.540
<i>all: ♪ All thumbs,</i>
<i>no thumbs ♪</i>

19:04.542 --> 19:05.574
<i>♪ Feels like a crime ♪</i>

19:05.576 --> 19:08.644
<i>♪ Can't pull on a zipper</i>
<i>or flip a dime ♪</i>

19:08.646 --> 19:10.112
<i>♪ And forget about chopsticks ♪</i>

19:10.114 --> 19:11.680
<i>♪ You'll starve every time ♪</i>

19:11.682 --> 19:14.550
<i>♪ Without your thumbs,</i>
<i>you're all thumbs ♪</i>

19:14.552 --> 19:16.785
<i>- ♪ Thumbs, thumbs, thumbs ♪</i>

19:16.787 --> 19:19.822
<i>all: ♪ Thumbs, thumbs, thumbs ♪</i>

19:19.824 --> 19:23.726
<i>- ♪ Without your thumbs ♪</i>

19:23.728 --> 19:27.796
<i>♪ You're all thumbs ♪</i>

19:27.798 --> 19:29.031
<i>- [whispering]</i>
<i>Thumbs, thumbs, thumbs.</i>

19:29.033 --> 19:31.600
- [knocking]
SpongeBob, it's me, Sandy!

19:31.602 --> 19:34.436
Hey, SpongeBob!
I haven't seen you in days.

19:34.438 --> 19:37.473
What'cha doin'?
- Waiting for autumn.

19:37.475 --> 19:39.775
- Come now,
it can't be that bad.

19:39.777 --> 19:42.077
- Leave me, Sandra.
Forget you ever knew me.

19:42.079 --> 19:46.415
Erase from your memory the face
of this useless sponge

19:46.417 --> 19:49.118
with these mutilated thumbs!

19:49.120 --> 19:51.820
- [gasps]
Don't give up, SpongeBob!

19:51.822 --> 19:54.657
You have to find
something you love.

19:54.659 --> 19:56.091
Something to live for.

19:56.093 --> 19:58.594
- Ha.
And what might that be?

19:58.596 --> 19:59.628
- I don't know, SpongeBob.

19:59.630 --> 20:04.500
That's a question
you have to answer for yourself.

20:04.502 --> 20:07.570
<i>[somber music]</i>

20:07.572 --> 20:08.437
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:08.439 --> 20:10.606
- Sandy?
Sandy.

20:10.608 --> 20:12.041
Sandy, come back!

20:12.043 --> 20:16.745
I need you to help me open
this jar of peanut butter!

20:16.747 --> 20:19.014
[straining]

20:19.016 --> 20:23.018
[glass shattering]
[sobbing]

20:23.420 --> 20:26.922
Enough sitting around
feeling sorry for myself.

20:26.924 --> 20:30.192
<i>[inspirational music]</i>

20:30.194 --> 20:38.133
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:38.135 --> 20:40.069
[straining]

20:40.071 --> 20:44.873
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:44.875 --> 20:47.876
- [shouting]

20:47.878 --> 20:51.213
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:52.115 --> 20:53.749
- Um...

20:53.751 --> 20:56.518
Oof.
Turn over.

20:56.520 --> 20:57.453
[meat sizzling]

20:57.455 --> 21:00.789
- My thumbs are better,
and I am ready to work.

21:00.791 --> 21:02.157
- The job's taken.

21:02.159 --> 21:04.193
- Well, I'm taking it back.

21:04.195 --> 21:06.996
- Just how you gonna do that?

21:06.998 --> 21:09.131
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

21:09.133 --> 21:10.766
- Thumb war.

21:10.768 --> 21:11.667
- En garde.

21:11.669 --> 21:14.069
together:
One, two, three, four.

21:14.071 --> 21:16.505
I declare a thumb war!

21:16.507 --> 21:17.973
[swords clanking]

21:17.975 --> 21:22.044
[both grunting and straining]

21:22.046 --> 21:30.586
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:32.222 --> 21:33.589
- Whoa!

21:33.591 --> 21:35.491
[all gasp]

21:35.493 --> 21:36.725
[swords clanking]

21:36.727 --> 21:38.961
- Ooh.
[shouts]

21:38.963 --> 21:42.564
Admit it.
You have been bested.

21:42.566 --> 21:43.899
- Never.

21:43.901 --> 21:46.935
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:46.937 --> 21:49.138
- Then prepare to be pinned.

21:49.140 --> 21:51.006
- [groaning]
- Don't give up.

21:51.008 --> 21:52.608
Something to live for.

21:52.610 --> 21:55.778
all: Something to live for!

21:55.780 --> 21:58.280
- [sucking]

22:00.583 --> 22:02.084
[swords clanking]

22:02.086 --> 22:04.053
all: Whoa!

22:04.055 --> 22:05.688
[both straining]

22:05.690 --> 22:07.056
[swords clash]
- Yeah!

22:07.058 --> 22:09.892
- SpongeBob wins!

22:09.894 --> 22:10.826
[all cheering]

22:10.828 --> 22:14.630
- SpongeBob,
you old patty jockey.

22:14.632 --> 22:16.665
Welcome home, son.

22:16.667 --> 22:20.636
- Uh, it's okay.
I hate work anyway.

22:20.638 --> 22:22.171
[laughter]

22:22.173 --> 22:22.938
- Oh, Patrick.

22:22.940 --> 22:25.908
- No, but really,
I do hate work.

22:25.910 --> 22:29.278
[laughter]

22:29.946 --> 22:32.047
- [laughing]

22:32.049 --> 22:34.750
Everybody's laughing!

22:34.752 --> 22:36.185
Oh, hey, SpongeBob.

22:36.187 --> 22:38.020
I got something for you.

22:38.022 --> 22:39.154
- Yes, Patrick?

22:39.156 --> 22:41.957
<i>[mellow music]</i>

22:41.959 --> 22:43.926
all: Ooh.

22:43.928 --> 22:46.128
[all cheering]

22:46.130 --> 22:49.331
[fireworks exploding]

